<TITLE> Sedition complaint filed over burning effigy of president </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhairab, Nov 5 (bdnews24.com)--A Kishoreganj Awami League leader on Thursday filed a complaint of sedition over the torching of the effigy of president Zillur Rahman and derogatory remarks against him on Nov 1, 2, police said. Bhairab police chief Mohammad Shahjahan Kabir told bdnews24.com Siraj Uddin, who is the acting AL president of Bhairab Upazila, filed the complaint. Siraj Uddin told bdnews24.com they also called for a half-day blockade of road, rail and river routes on Tuesday demanding the trial for the guilty. A citizen committee, 'Kishoreganj Akhandata Rakkha Sangram Parisad' enforced a dawn-to-dusk shutdown on Nov 2 and a black flag-hoisting programme the day before, protesting the government move to curve out Bhairab from Kishoreganj and make it a district. "The comaplaint has been sent to the home ministry for review. It will be filed as a sedition case after a clearance from the home ministry," Kabir said. No one has been specifically mentioned as accused in the charge, but will be made after finding them out through investigation, Kabir said. bdn
